Leicester City forward, Kelechi Iheanacho has been included in the Premier League Team of the Week. Iheanacho scored once and provided two assists in Leicester City’s 4-2 away win at Aston Villa last Saturday. It was the 26-year-old’s second goal in 15 league outings for the Foxes this season. It was the first time he will be included in the Team of the Week this season. Iheanacho was also named Man of the Match after the game. He is the only Leicester City player included in the selection.